findings.title: IngestImpl.sol: Use of transfer() instead of call()
findings.description: The code uses `transfer()` when sending ETH to `to` / `sendTo`, which only forwards 2300 gas. In cases where `sendTo` address is a smart contract whose fallback function consumes more than 2300 gas, the call will always fail.

findings.title: Incorrect and inconsistent spelling of the word "implementation"
findings.description: The word implementation is mispelled in variable names in the contracts `IngestImpl.sol` and `IngestRegistry.sol`.
